Description of adult female. Total body length of holotype 1.03 mm ; paratypes 1.06–1.30 mm , mean 1.2 mm (n = 4 ). Body (
Fig. 2
) elongate, heavily chitinised and perforated, thoracic and abdominal segments telescoping into each other to varying degrees, 9.2 times as long as wide. In lateral view, abdominal segments wider than thoracic segments. Head 1.3 times as long as wide, 11.5 % longer than first 3 thoracic segments combined.
